Program: Outlook
Title: 22/02/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0067vy1
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 23 Feb 2010
Sarah Taylor Sarah Taylor's daughter Nadia was kidnapped from the UK by her father and taken to Libya. Sarah tells Ritula Shah about her three year fight to get her back and the help that she received from Libyan leader Colonel Gaddafi and from British Prime Ministers Tony Blair and then Gordon Brown. Rio Favela Police Outlook's Alphonso Daniels visits the Santa Marta slum in Rio de Janeiro to find out about the permanent "pacifier" police force that is now based there. How successful has it been and can it be expanded to the rest of the city before the 2016 Olympics? Peter Colat Peter Colat has just broken the world record for holding his breath underwater. He managed a staggering 19 minutes and 21 seconds. Peter tells Ritula Shah how he did it. Show less